---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
---

<PageLayout 
  title="Case Study: 1950s Block Foundation Restoration North York | $14,500 | Dryspace"
  description="Detailed case study of a cement block foundation waterproofing project in North York. See the complete process, costs, and 3-year results."
>
  <main class="flex-grow">
    <section class="bg-slate-50 text-slate-900 py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="mb-4">
          <a href="/case-studies" class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300">← Back to Case Studies</a>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">
          1950s Cement Block Foundation Complete Restoration
        </h1>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm">
          <span class="bg-white/10 px-3 py-1 ">North York, Toronto</span>
          <span class="bg-white/10 px-3 py-1 ">April 2024</span>
          <span class="bg-cyan-600/30 px-3 py-1 ">Total Cost: $14,500</span>
          <span class="bg-amber-500/30 px-3 py-1 ">Duration: 5 Days</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-12">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-red-800">The Challenge</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            This 1950s North York home with hollow-core cement block foundation experienced severe water infiltration 
            through deteriorated mortar joints. The homeowner had attempted DIY repairs with hydraulic cement, 
            which failed within months. Water was entering through multiple points, causing mold growth and 
            threatening $30,000 worth of finished basement renovations.
          </p>
          
          <div class="mt-6">
            <img src="/assets/waterproofing/crack on foundation wall due winter freeze.webp" 
                 alt="Foundation crack caused by winter freeze-thaw cycles in North York block foundation" 
                 loading="lazy" 
                 class="  w-full" / width="800" height="600" decoding="async">
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-2 text-center">Foundation crack caused by winter freeze-thaw cycles - a common issue in block foundations</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose max-w-none">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Property Details</h2>
          
          <div class="bg-slate-50  p-6 mb-8">
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Home Specifications</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600">
                  <li><strong>Built:</strong> 1953</li>
                  <li><strong>Foundation Type:</strong> 8" hollow-core cement blocks</li>
                  <li><strong>Basement Size:</strong> 1,200 sq ft</li>
                  <li><strong>Foundation Perimeter:</strong> 140 linear feet</li>
                  <li><strong>Depth Below Grade:</strong> 7 feet</li>
                  <li><strong>Soil Type:</strong> Clay (poor drainage)</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Water Issues Identified</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600">
                  <li>• 40% of mortar joints deteriorated</li>
                  <li>• Step cracks in 3 corners</li>
                  <li>• Water filling hollow block cores</li>
                  <li>• Efflorescence on 60% of wall surface</li>
                  <li>• Failed DIY patches in 8 locations</li>
                  <li>• Mold growth behind drywall</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Initial Assessment Findings</h2>
          
          <div class="bg-amber-50  p-6 mb-8">
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Critical Issues Discovered:</h3>
            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-slate-600">
              <li>
                <strong>Mortar Joint Failure:</strong> Original lime-based mortar from 1953 had reached end of life. 
                Joints were soft, crumbling, and allowing direct water penetration.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Hollow Core Water Accumulation:</strong> Water was filling the hollow cores of blocks, 
                traveling internally, and emerging at floor level 10+ feet from entry point.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>No Waterproofing Membrane:</strong> Original construction had only parging, which had 
                delaminated in multiple areas.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Inadequate Drainage:</strong> Original clay tile drain was 70% blocked with sediment.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Grade Issues:</strong> Landscaping had raised grade, directing water toward foundation.
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Our Solution: Comprehensive Interior & Exterior Approach</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
            <div class="border-l-4 border-cyan-500 pl-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Phase 1: Interior Waterproofing (Days 1-2)</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600">
                <li>• Removed 18" of drywall along perimeter to access foundation</li>
                <li>• Drilled weep holes at base of hollow cores to drain trapped water (87 holes total)</li>
                <li>• Installed WaterGuard® interior drainage system along 140 linear feet</li>
                <li>• Connected drainage to new TripleSafe™ sump pump system with battery backup</li>
                <li>• Applied crystalline waterproofing coating to interior block walls</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-cyan-500 pl-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Phase 2: Critical Repairs (Day 3)</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600">
                <li>• Repointed deteriorated mortar joints with Type N mortar (420 linear feet)</li>
                <li>• Injected polyurethane into step cracks (3 locations, 18 linear feet total)</li>
                <li>• Core-filled bottom 3 courses of blocks with concrete for stability</li>
                <li>• Installed carbon fiber strips at corners for reinforcement</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-cyan-500 pl-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Phase 3: Exterior Protection (Days 4-5)</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600">
                <li>• Excavated problem areas (north and east walls, 70 linear feet)</li>
                <li>• Applied rubberized membrane to exterior block surface</li>
                <li>• Installed dimple board drainage mat for additional protection</li>
                <li>• Replaced sections of weeping tile and connected to interior system</li>
                <li>• Backfilled with 3/4" clear gravel and proper grading</li>
              </ul>
              
              <div class="mt-6">
                <img src="/assets/waterproofing/dimpled membrane on base of footing.webp" 
                     alt="Dimpled membrane installation on foundation footing for exterior waterproofing" 
                     loading="lazy" 
                     class="  w-full" / width="800" height="600" decoding="async">
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-2 text-center">Dimpled membrane properly installed at the base of the footing for optimal drainage</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Technical Specifications</h2>
          
          <div class="bg-slate-50  p-6 mb-8">
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Materials Used</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-600">
                  <li>• 140 ft WaterGuard® drainage channel</li>
                  <li>• 1 TripleSafe™ sump system</li>
                  <li>• 180 Ah battery backup system</li>
                  <li>• 8 gallons polyurethane injection resin</li>
                  <li>• 35 bags Type N mortar mix</li>
                  <li>• 4 yards concrete for core filling</li>
                  <li>• 700 sq ft rubberized membrane</li>
                  <li>• 700 sq ft dimple drainage board</li>
                  <li>• 12 yards 3/4" clear gravel</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Equipment Deployed</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-600">
                  <li>• Mini excavator (Kubota KX040)</li>
                  <li>• Concrete saw for interior trenching</li>
                  <li>• Core drilling equipment</li>
                  <li>• Injection pump (2000 PSI)</li>
                  <li>• Industrial dehumidifiers (2 units)</li>
                  <li>• HEPA air scrubbers for dust control</li>
                  <li>• Mortar mixer and pumping equipment</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Cost Breakdown</h2>
          
          <div class="bg-cyan-50  p-6 mb-8">
            <table class="w-full">
              <thead>
                <tr class="border-b-2 border-cyan-200">
                  <th class="text-left py-2">Component</th>
                  <th class="text-right py-2">Cost</th>
                  <th class="text-right py-2">% of Total</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="divide-y divide-green-100">
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-2">Interior drainage system</td>
                  <td class="text-right">$4,200</td>
                  <td class="text-right">29%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-2">Sump pump with battery backup</td>
                  <td class="text-right">$2,500</td>
                  <td class="text-right">17%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-2">Mortar joint repairs</td>
                  <td class="text-right">$2,100</td>
                  <td class="text-right">14%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-2">Crack injection</td>
                  <td class="text-right">$1,200</td>
                  <td class="text-right">8%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-2">Exterior waterproofing (partial)</td>
                  <td class="text-right">$3,500</td>
                  <td class="text-right">24%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-2">Concrete restoration</td>
                  <td class="text-right">$800</td>
                  <td class="text-right">6%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-2">Permits and disposal</td>
                  <td class="text-right">$200</td>
                  <td class="text-right">2%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="font-bold border-t-2 border-cyan-200">
                  <td class="py-2">Total Project Cost</td>
                  <td class="text-right">$14,500</td>
                  <td class="text-right">100%</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            
            <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-cyan-50 rounded">
              <p class="text-sm text-cyan-700">
                <strong>Financing:</strong> Homeowner used 12-month 0% financing. Monthly payment: $1,208
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-8">
            <img src="/assets/waterproofing/waterproofing + insuulation of foundation walls styrofoam.webp" 
                 alt="Waterproofing and insulation of foundation walls with styrofoam" 
                 loading="lazy" 
                 class="  w-full" / width="800" height="600" decoding="async">
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-2 text-center">Complete waterproofing and insulation system for optimal foundation protection</p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Results & Follow-Up</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
            <div class="bg-amber-500  p-6">
              <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Immediate Results (First 30 Days)</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600">
                <li> Complete elimination of water infiltration</li>
                <li> Basement humidity dropped from 78% to 45%</li>
                <li> No water accumulation during April 2024 storms (4.2" rainfall)</li>
                <li> Mold remediation successful with no regrowth</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-amber-500  p-6">
              <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">6-Month Follow-Up (October 2024)</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600">
                <li> System handled fall storms without issues</li>
                <li> Sump pump cycling normally (4-6 times daily during rain)</li>
                <li> No new cracks or mortar deterioration</li>
                <li> Homeowner completed basement refinishing ($18,000 investment)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-amber-500  p-6">
              <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Current Status (3 Years Later)</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600">
                <li> Zero water infiltration events</li>
                <li> Annual maintenance performed (pump cleaned, battery tested)</li>
                <li> Home value increased by $45,000 (appraiser noted dry basement)</li>
                <li> Insurance premium reduced by $280/year</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Lessons Learned</h2>
          
          <div class="bg-orange-50  p-6 mb-8">
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Key Takeaways from This Project:</h3>
            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-slate-600">
              <li>
                <strong>Hollow block foundations require special attention:</strong> Water trapped in cores must 
                be addressed with weep holes and proper drainage.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>DIY repairs often make problems worse:</strong> Improper hydraulic cement application 
                trapped water inside blocks, accelerating deterioration.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Combined approach most effective:</strong> Interior drainage handles groundwater while 
                exterior protection prevents infiltration.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Mortar joint maintenance critical:</strong> Repointing every 25-30 years prevents 
                major structural issues.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Early intervention saves money:</strong> Addressing issues before basement finishing 
                saved estimated $20,000 in remediation costs.
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Homeowner Testimonial</h2>
          
          <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-orange-500 pl-6 italic text-slate-600 mb-8">
            "After trying to fix the water issues myself for 2 years, I finally called Dryspace. They identified 
            problems I never knew existed - water was traveling through the hollow blocks and emerging far from 
            where it entered. The crew was professional, explained everything, and cleaned up daily. Three years 
            later, our basement is still bone dry. The peace of mind was worth every penny, especially after we 
            invested in finishing the basement. Our home value increased significantly, and we even got an 
            insurance discount. I wish I had called them sooner!"
            <footer class="mt-4 font-bold not-italic">— David & Sarah M., North York</footer>
          </blockquote>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Similar Foundation? Here's What You Should Know</h2>
          
          <div class="bg-slate-50  p-6 mb-8">
            <p class="mb-4">
              If your home has a cement block foundation (common in Toronto homes built 1940-1970), watch for these warning signs:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600 mb-4">
              <li>• White chalky deposits (efflorescence) on block surfaces</li>
              <li>• Horizontal or step cracks following mortar lines</li>
              <li>• Water appearing at floor level with no visible source above</li>
              <li>• Deteriorating mortar that crumbles when touched</li>
              <li>• Musty smell even after dehumidifying</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="font-bold text-orange-600">
              Early intervention typically costs 50-70% less than waiting until severe damage occurs.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-50 text-slate-900  p-8 text-center">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Facing Similar Water Issues?</h2>
          <p class="mb-6">
            Get a professional assessment before small problems become expensive disasters. 
            Our inspection identifies all water entry points and provides a detailed solution plan.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
            <a href="/contact" class="bg-white text-orange-600 px-8 py-3  font-bold hover:bg-slate-50 transition duration-300">
              Schedule Free Inspection
            </a>
            <a href="tel:437-545-0067" class="border-2 border-white px-8 py-3  font-bold hover:bg-white hover:text-orange-600 transition duration-300">
              Call: 437-545-0067
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Content Section -->
    <section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Related Services & Resources</h2>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
          <a href="/services/foundation-repair" class="block p-6 bg-white  shadow hover: transition">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-orange-600">Foundation Crack Repair</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-500">Professional injection services like those used in this project.</p>
            <span class="text-cyan-600 text-sm mt-2 inline-block">View Service →</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/services/interior-waterproofing" class="block p-6 bg-white  shadow hover: transition">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-orange-600">Interior Waterproofing</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-500">Complete interior drainage systems we installed here.</p>
            <span class="text-cyan-600 text-sm mt-2 inline-block">View Service →</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/services/sump-pump-installation" class="block p-6 bg-white  shadow hover: transition">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-orange-600">Sump Pump Systems</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-500">TripleSafe system like the one in this case study.</p>
            <span class="text-cyan-600 text-sm mt-2 inline-block">View Service →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="p-6 bg-amber-500 ">
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Planning Tools</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              <li> <a href="/tools/waterproofing-cost-calculator" class="text-cyan-600 hover:underline">Calculate Your Project Cost</a></li>
              <li> <a href="/resources/foundation-types-guide" class="text-cyan-600 hover:underline">Block Foundation Guide</a></li>
              <li> <a href="/financing" class="text-cyan-600 hover:underline">12-Month 0% Financing Available</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 bg-orange-50 ">
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">More Case Studies</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              <li> <a href="/case-studies/stone-foundation-cabbagetown" class="text-cyan-600 hover:underline">Historic Stone Foundation</a></li>
              <li> <a href="/case-studies/diy-disaster-recovery" class="text-cyan-600 hover:underline">DIY Repair Gone Wrong</a></li>
              <li> <a href="/locations/toronto" class="text-cyan-600 hover:underline">More North York Projects</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <ContactForm />
  </main>
</PageLayout>